            What DrySpace Uses &amp; Why
          </h2>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-600 mb-8">
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
              After completing hundreds of exterior waterproofing projects across Toronto, North York, Scarborough, and the GTA, we've developed proven membrane system specifications optimized for our climate and soil conditions. Here's our approach for different scenarios:
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Exterior System -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200/60 shadow-card p-6">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
                <div class="bg-cyan-500 text-white rounded-lg p-3 flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Standard Exterior Waterproofing (Our Recommendation)</h3>
                  <div class="bg-cyan-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
                    <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">System: Blueskin WP 200 + Delta-MS Drainage Board</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">Total cost: $12-$18 per sq ft installed</p>
                  </div>
                  <p class="text-slate-600 mb-3 leading-relaxed">
                    For 95% of residential projects, this proven combination delivers the best balance of performance, longevity, and value. We apply Blueskin WP 200 sheet membrane (60 mil rubberized asphalt) directly to properly prepared concrete walls, then install Delta-MS dimple drainage board as a protection layer. This two-layer system provides redundant protection: the Blueskin is your waterproof barrier, while the Delta-MS protects it from backfill damage and channels any infiltrated water down to the weeping tile.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    <strong>Why this system wins:</strong> Blueskin has an outstanding track record in Toronto's freeze-thaw cycles, and the Delta-MS drainage dramatically reduces hydrostatic pressure. We can guarantee this system for 25 years because we've seen it perform flawlessly for decades in our harshest conditions.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
